void aho_corasick_suffix_link() {

void aho_corasick_suffix_link_aux(s: Node) {
    for each edge(c, v):
        t = f(s)
        while(t > 0 && t.cannotRead(c)) t = f(t)
        
        if (t.canRead(c)) {
            t = t.get(c)
            f(v) = t
        } else {
            f(v) = 0;
        }
        aho_corasick_suffix_link_aux(v);
}  ^8HAcQ9tr

void aho_corasick_suffix_link_aux(s: Node) {
    for each edge(c, v) {
        if (s!=0) {
            t = f(s)
            while(t > 0 && t.cannotRead(c)) t = f(t)
            
            if (t.canRead(c)) {
                t = t.get(c)
                f(v) = t
            } else {
                f(v) = 0;
            }
        }
        aho_corasick_suffix_link_aux(v);
    }
}  ^ZNLuMlhS

void aho_corasick_suffix_link_aux(s: Node) {
    for each edge(c, v) {
        if (s!=0) {
            t = f(s)
            while(t > 0 && t.cannotRead(c)) t = f(t)
            
            if (t.canRead(c)) {
                t = t.get(c)
                f(v) = t
            } else {
                f(v) = 0;
            }
        }
        aho_corasick_suffix_link_aux(v);
    }
}  ^dNZODnAX

we will visit each node to calculate by calling the aux function on that node itself exactly once.
Hence the total time complexity(excluding the while loop) = O(N)
the only times where t increases is when a character is successfully matched, 
in which case t points to the node that is connected by the edge that is read.

in the worst case that every character in the trie is the same character and we always fallback
